record.title: RECOGNIZING THE NAVY SEALS MUSEUM IN FORT PIERCE, FLORIDA
record.narrative:
RECOGNIZING THE NAVY SEALS MUSEUM IN FORT PIERCE, FLORIDA -- (Senate - October 31, 2007)

[Page: S13646]

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the Armed Services Committee be discharged from further consideration of H.R. 2779 and the Senate then proceed to its consideration.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered. The clerk will state the bill by title.
record.narrative: The legislative clerk read as follows:
A bill (H.R. 2779) to recognize the Navy UDT-SEAL Museum in Fort Pierce, FL, as the official national museum of Navy SEALs and their predecessors.
There being no objection, the Senate proceeded to consider the bill.

speaking.paragraph: Mr. President, I ask unanimous consent that the bill be read the third time, passed, and the motion to reconsider be laid upon the table; that any statements relating thereto be printed in the Record.

record.chair: Without objection, it is so ordered.
The bill (H.R. 2779) was ordered to a third reading, was read the third time, and passed.
